# Vanilla Frontend Rules

The frontend is a lightweight static developer portal.

Use only:
- HTML
- CSS
- Vanilla JavaScript
- Fetch API
- Simple browser globals when needed

Do not add:
- React, Angular, Vue, Svelte, or other frameworks
- npm dependencies
- bundlers or build tools
- TypeScript compilation
- frontend routers
- state management libraries

Preferred script order:
```html
<script src="js/env.js" defer></script>
<script src="js/state.js" defer></script>
<script src="js/rest-service.js" defer></script>
<script src="js/app.js" defer></script>
```

Allowed globals:
- `window.CONFIG`
- `window.PrairieLogState`
- `window.restService`
- `window.PrairieLogUI`

Avoid random global variables. Keep page-specific logic in page-specific scripts.
